The 26-year-old victim was killed outside a shop in Cleary Park in Port Elizabeths northern areas. CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating after a man was shot dead in a suspected gang-related shooting in Port Elizabeth s northern areas.The 26-year-old victim was killed outside a shop in Cleary Park earlier this week after buying food.He was allegedly affiliated to the G-Star gang.The police's Priscilla Naidu says: The owner of the shop heard three gunshots being fired at the exit of the shop. A while later, the owner found a person was lying on his back with gunshot wounds. The person was already dead. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)